GUIDELINES:

To qualify for a community grant from the Foundation, a 501 (c) 3 organization must fall within one of our four strategic areas and deliver services in one of U.S. regional communities where we have operations.

FOCUS AREAS OF GIVING 

  • Youth and Education: programs that promote youth development, particularly for youth at-risk
  • Civic & Community Development: affordable housing, work readiness, crisis assistance and hunger relief
  • Environment & Conservation: hands-on environmental learning programs
  • Arts & Culture: arts education for children and youth as well as support for museums and the performing arts

RESTRICTIONS:

Contributions will not be made to or in support of: 

  • Individuals
  • Sectarian/denominational religious organizations, except where funds are to be used in direct interest of the entire community
  • Loans or investments *Political/lobbying organizations
  • Industry, trade or professional association memberships
  • Disease-specific or health related organizations
  • Sports/athletic programs and facilities
  • Fundraising events/sponsorships

  • I confirm my organization is not requesting 75% or more of its general operating dollars.
  • I confirm this request is for general operating or program support rather than only special events (i.e. dinners and tickets).
  • I confirm for annual support it has been 1 year since our last gift and for a major gift it has been 4 years.
  • I confirm my organization is not one of the following:
    • Athletes or athletic organizations
    • Conference or seminar attendance
    • Courtesy or goodwill advertising in benefit publications
    • Fellowships
    • Fraternal organizations (police, fire associations, Greek letter societies)
    • Individual K-12 schools or PTA
    • Individuals

    • Political parties, campaigns or candidates, partisan political organizations
    • Private foundations
    • Sectarian, religious and denominational organizations, except for specific programs that are broadly promoted, available to anyone, and free from religious orientation
    • Service Club or organizations(Kiwanis, Rotary, Optimist) raising money

  • I confirm if this is an annual request for Des Moines, Global Locations, and National Programs it is at or greater than $10,000.
  • I confirm if this is a large capital or innovative program enhancement for a Major gift it is at or greater than $100,000.

GUIDELINES:

To qualify for a community grant from the Foundation, a 501 (c) 3 organization must fall within one of our four strategic areas and deliver services in one of U.S. regional communities where we have operations.

FOCUS AREAS OF GIVING 

  • Youth and Education: programs that promote youth development, particularly for youth at-risk
  • Civic & Community Development: affordable housing, work readiness, crisis assistance and hunger relief
  • Environment & Conservation: hands-on environmental learning programs
  • Arts & Culture: arts education for children and youth as well as support for museums and the performing arts

RESTRICTIONS:

Contributions will not be made to or in support of: 

  • Individuals
  • Sectarian/denominational religious organizations, except where funds are to be used in direct interest of the entire community
  • Loans or investments *Political/lobbying organizations
  • Industry, trade or professional association memberships
  • Disease-specific or health related organizations
  • Sports/athletic programs and facilities
  • Fundraising events/sponsorships

Instructions to Grant Specialist:

  1. Click "HCA Hope Fund Grant Request Application"  and "HCA Hope Fund - Grant Leader Recommendation Form" under Application Forms on the left to review the original application and the Grant Leaders recommendation. 
  2. After reviewing the application and Grant Leader recommendation, come back to this form by clicking "HCA Hope Fund - Grant Specialist Recommendation Form" under the Application Forms section on the left and choose "Edit" to complete the form.
  3. Click "Submit" at the top of the form to save your changes. (Note: The form will save as you complete it but you must click 'Submit' to be able to activate the approve or decline buttons.)

Instructions to Grant Specialist:

  1. Click "HCA Hope Fund Grant Request Application"  and "HCA Hope Fund - Grant Leader Recommendation Form" under Application Forms on the left to review the original application and the Grant Leaders recommendation. 
  2. After reviewing the application and Grant Leader recommendation, come back to this form by clicking "HCA Hope Fund - Grant Specialist Recommendation Form" under the Application Forms section on the left and choose "Edit" to complete the form.
  3. Click "Submit" at the top of the form to save your changes. (Note: The form will save as you complete it but you must click 'Submit' to be able to activate the approve or decline buttons.)
